org.apache.flink.runtime.instance

类 InstanceConnectionInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.flink.runtime.instance.InstanceConnectionInfo
  • 所有已实现的接口:
    Serializable, Comparable<InstanceConnectionInfo>, org.apache.flink.core.io.IOReadableWritable

    public class InstanceConnectionInfo
extends Object
implements org.apache.flink.core.io.IOReadableWritable, Comparable<InstanceConnectionInfo>, Serializable
    This class encapsulates the connection information of a TaskManager. It describes the host where the TaskManager operates and its server port for data exchange. This class also contains utilities to work with the TaskManager's host name, which is used to localize work assignments.

      • InstanceConnectionInfo

        public InstanceConnectionInfo(InetAddress inetAddress,
                              int dataPort)
        Constructs a new instance connection info object. The constructor will attempt to retrieve the instance's host name and domain name through the operating system's lookup mechanisms.
        参数:
        inetAddress - the network address the instance's task manager binds its sockets to
        dataPort - the port instance's task manager expects to receive transfer envelopes on

      • getFQDNHostname

        public String getFQDNHostname()
        Returns the fully-qualified domain name the TaskManager. If the name could not be determined, the return value will be a textual representation of the TaskManager's IP address.
        返回:
        The fully-qualified domain name of the TaskManager.

      • getHostname

        public String getHostname()
        Gets the hostname of the TaskManager. The hostname derives from the fully qualified domain name (FQDN, see getFQDNHostname()):
        • If the FQDN is the textual IP address, then the hostname is also the IP address
        • If the FQDN has only one segment (such as "localhost", or "host17"), then this is used as the hostname.
        • If the FQDN has multiple segments (such as "worker3.subgroup.company.net"), then the first segment (here "worker3") will be used as the hostname.
        返回:
        The hostname of the TaskManager.

      • getInetAdress

        public String getInetAdress()
        Gets the IP address where the TaskManager operates.
        返回:
        The IP address.
